%20course%20that%20I%20bought.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22d2eb4c3a-cae8-4649-9bcb-676a417ae084%5C%22%3ELearning%20to%20code%20was%20tough%20but%20really%20exciting%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20my%2012-hour%20shifts%2C%20there%20wasn't%20much%20to%20do%20besides%20work%20out%20or%20study.%20I%20studied%20every%20single%20day%20for%20three%20hours.%20I%20was%20having%20a%20good%20time%20and%20making%20progress.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20blended%20my%20background%20as%20an%20intelligence%20analyst%20with%20my%20ability%20to%20write%20code%2C%20which%20is%20how%20I%20started%20working%20on%20some%20technical%20coding%20projects%20in%20my%20intelligence%20job.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20that%2C%20I%20used%20it%20to%20land%20my%20temporary%20duty%20assignment%20with%20Section%2031%2C%20an%20Air%20Force%20unit%20in%20Southern%20California%20tasked%20with%20creating%20applications%20for%20the%20Space%20Force.%20I%20was%20simultaneously%20an%20intelligence%20analyst%20and%20a%20software%20engineer.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%222549e731-5f83-4cc9-b00a-11698bf453b0%5C%22%3EMy%20doubt%20lasted%20for%20over%20half%20of%20the%20apprenticeship%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20feeling%20of%20doubt%20lasted%20for%20around%20three%20and%20a%20half%20months.%20It%20eventually%20clicked%20for%20me%20that%20I%20wasn't%20supposed%20to%20get%20it%20that%20quickly.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20grew%20up%20playing%20sports%2C%20and%20I%20thought%20of%20learning%20to%20code%20as%20learning%20sports.%20I%20had%20only%20been%20learning%20to%20code%20for%20about%20a%20year%2C%20and%20I%20was%20working%20alongside%20people%20who%20had%20been%20working%20in%20the%20industry%20for%20longer.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20had%20to%20realize%20that's%20OK.%20They're%20not%20expecting%20me%20to%20be%20a%20professional%20coder%2C%20but%20they%20want%20me%20to%20learn%20and%20grow.%20That's%20when%20I%20finally%20started%20to%20turn%20a%20corner%20and%20realize%20that%20I%20need%20to%20increase%20my%20reps%2C%20study%2C%20and%20practice%20like%20I%20would%20a%20sport.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%223452c635-f4aa-4c0e-8177-1d58239df89b%5C%22%3EHaving%20a%20mentor%20really%20helped%20me%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20I%20got%20a%20mentor%2C%20he%20streamlined%20everything%20I%20learned%2C%20helped%20me%20apply%20it%2C%20and%20told%20me%20what%20I%20didn't%20need%20to%20learn.%20Finding%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhy-the-right-mentor-could-supercharge-your-career-2023-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ementor%3C%2Fa%3E%20I%20was%20comfortable%20with%20and%20someone%20who%20had%20already%20achieved%20success%20where%20I%20wanted%20to%20achieve%20success%20was%20probably%20the%20most%20important%20part%20of%20my%20learning.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20I%20returned%20home%20from%20Iraq%2C%20I%20had%20two%20mentors.%20One%20was%20in%20the%20Air%20Force%2C%20a%20senior%20engineer%20in%20my%20squadron%2C%20and%20I%20just%20attached%20myself%20to%20him%20and%20asked%20him%20so%20many%20questions.%20He%20was%20so%20patient%20with%20me.%20I%20had%20another%20mentor%20who%20was%20a%20civilian.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20have%20some%20mentors%20now%20at%20Slack%20who%20are%20able%20to%20challenge%20me%20and%20help%20me%20grow.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22273fe884-ac82-493d-a36e-4f302d5add78%5C%22%3EThere's%20not%20a%20single%20thing%20I%20would%20do%20differently%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI'm%20extremely%20grateful%20and%20blessed%20to%20be%20in%20the%20position%20I'm%20in%20today.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20Space%20Force%20apprenticeship%2C%20I%20did%20pair%20programming%2C%20which%20means%20you%20sit%20with%20another%20engineer%20and%20go%20back%20and%20forth.%20One%20writes%20the%20technical%20test%2C%20and%20the%20other%20writes%20the%20code%20to%20make%20that%20test%20pass.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEvery%20time%20I%20heard%20a%20phrase%20that%20I%20didn't%20know%20in%20a%20meeting%20or%20saw%20a%20line%20of%20code%20that%20I%20didn't%20understand%2C%20I%20made%20note%20of%20it.%20Then%2C%20for%2030%20minutes%20every%20single%20day%2C%20I%20would%20talk%20to%20my%20mentor%20and%20just%20try%20to%20get%20better.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20you're%20feeling%20impostor%20syndrome%2C%20look%20in%20the%20mirror%20and%20tell%20yourself%20that%20the%20people%20who%20hired%20you%20are%20smart%20people%2C%20and%20they%20hired%20you%20for%20a%20reason.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20a%20staff%20developer%20advocate%20now%2C%20it's%20my%20job%20to%20know%20how%20to%20create%20custom%20applications%20in%20Slack%20and%20then%20teach%20them%20to%20all%20of%20our%20customers%20around%20the%20world%20with%20content%20via%20on-site%20workshops%2C%20presentations%2C%20keynotes%2C%20and%20virtual%20content.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22dededc7e-974e-4fc2-98e8-528b054024ee%5C%22%3EIn%202020%2C%20I%20started%20a%20YouTube%20channel%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20documented%20my%20process%20and%20created%20content%20about%20software%20engineering.%20When%20I%20was%20separating%20from%20the%20Air%20Force%20in%202022%2C%20I%20put%20out%20a%20little%20teaser%20video%20on%20Twitter%20saying%20that%20I%20was%20open%20to%20work.%20That%20post%20went%20pretty%20viral%2C%20and%20I%20got%20messages%20about%20job%20opportunities%20at%20Google%2C%20Amazon%2C%20and%20Slack%2C%20where%20I%20ended%20up.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20don't%20have%20impostor%20syndrome%20anymore%20because%20I%20understand%20what%20it%20is.%20The%20only%20way%20to%20get%20through%20it%20is%20by%20being%20confident%20in%20your%20abilities.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI'm%20now%20confident%20in%20my%20abilities%20and%20what%20I%20can%20offer%20my%20employer%20and%20my%20community.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EDid%20you%20land%20a%20job%20without%20a%20college%20degree%3F%20Reach%20out%20to%20this%20reporter%20at%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22mailto%3Amhoff%40businessinsider.com%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3Emhoff%40businessinsider.com%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%2