p%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%229e092b2a-aff3-4a97-9e3c-83ab397ac594%5C%22%3EHow%20other%20US%20cities%20have%20fared%20without%20fares%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EKansas%20City%20was%20the%20first%20major%20metro%20in%20the%20US%20to%20fully%20support%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.kcur.org%2Fgovernment%2F2019-12-05%2Fkansas-city-council-unanimously-votes-to-get-rid-of-bus-fares%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efree%20fares%20in%202019%2C%3C%2Fa%3E%20with%20Boston%20following%20in%202022%20with%20a%20few%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.boston.gov%2Fnews%2Ffree-fares-bus-routes-23-28-and-29-extended-two-more-years%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eprominent%20routes%20eliminating%20fees%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Some%20smaller%20cities%2C%20like%20Alexandria%2C%20Virginia%2C%20and%20Tucson%2C%20Arizona%2C%20have%20also%20implemented%20free%20bus%20rides%2C%20but%20not%20at%20the%20scale%20of%20Mamdani's%20plan.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20Kansas%20City%2C%20reports%20of%20safety%20and%20security%20incidents%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.marc.org%2Fsites%2Fdefault%2Ffiles%2F2022-04%2FTransit-Zero-Fare-Impact-Analysis.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edropped%20by%2039%25%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20the%20first%20year%20of%20zero-fare%20rides.%20Riders%20in%20Boston%20also%20saved%2C%20on%20average%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.boston.gov%2Fnews%2Ffree-fares-bus-routes-23-28-and-29-extended-two-more-years%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%2435%20a%20month%3C%2Fa%3E%20through%20the%20first%20year%20of%20implementation%2C%20according%20to%20a%20press%20release%20from%20the%20Boston%20Transportation%20Department.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EKansas%20City%20bus%20riders%20like%20Joy%20Mart%2C%20a%2028-year-old%20software%20engineer%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider%20the%20program%20is%20essential%2C%20especially%20for%20those%20looking%20for%20a%20job%20or%20on%20a%20fixed%20income.%20Mart%20lost%20their%20job%20a%20few%20years%20ago%2C%20and%20said%20that%20as%20a%20newcomer%20to%20Kansas%20City%2C%20the%20free%20buses%20helped%20them%20tremendously.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20was%20just%20so%20helpful%2C%20since%20you%20know%2C%20we're%20counting%20pennies%20at%20that%20point%2C%26quot%3B%20Mart%20said.%20Riders%20previously%20paid%20%2450%20for%20a%20monthly%20pass%20or%20%241.50%20per%20ride.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMart%20is%20a%20leader%20with%20Sunrise%20Movement%20KC%2C%20an%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fsunrisemvmtkc.carrd.co%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eactivist%20group%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20advocates%20for%20economic%2C%20climate%2C%20and%20racial%20justice.%20The%20group%20also%20supports%20and%20is%20petitioning%20for%20zero-fare%20buses%20at%20a%20time%20when%20some%20of%20its%20critics'%20biggest%20concerns%20are%20playing%20out.%20Due%20to%20budget%20shortfalls%2C%20Kansas%20City%20Mayor%20Quinton%20Lucas%20and%20the%20City%20Council%20approved%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.kcur.org%2Fnews%2F2025-04-04%2Fkansas-city-will-reinstate-bus-fares-and-reduce-frequency-of-most-routes-under-funding-plan%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ereimplementing%20%242%20fares%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20avoid%20major%20service%20cuts%20and%20driver%20layoffs.%20While%20the%20city%20already%20funded%20free%20buses%20for%20the%20next%20six%20months%2C%20after%20this%20period%2C%20the%20City%20Council%20will%20either%20rescind%20its%20plans%20or%20move%20forward%20with%20cutting%20services%20and%20bringing%20back%20fares.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIndeed%2C%20funding%20remains%20the%20largest%20hurdle%20for%20many%20cities.%20Kansas%20City%20residents%20already%20pay%20for%20the%20free%20bus%20system%20through%20a%20sales%20tax%20reallocation.%20The%20%E2%85%9C-cent%20sales%20tax%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fridekc.org%2Fnews%2Fvoters-say-yes-to-bus-tax-renewal%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efunded%3C%2Fa%3E%20about%2030%25%20of%20the%20free%20bus%20fare%20program%20and%20will%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.kcata.org%2Fnews%2Fvoters-say-yes-to-bus-tax-renewal%3Futm_source%3Dchatgpt.com%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Econtinue%20through%202034%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20according%20to%20the%20Kansas%20City%20Area%20Transportation%20Authority.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20New%20York%2C%20the%20mayor%20doesn't%20have%20control%20over%20the%20MTA%2C%20which%20is%20a%20state%20agency%2C%20but%20Mamdani%20has%20said%20he%20hopes%20to%20partially%20fund%20the%20program%20in%20part%20by%20collecting%20overdue%20fines%20on%20landlords.%20A%20spokesperson%20for%20the%20Mamdani%20campaign%20didn't%20immediately%20return%20BI's%20request%20for%20comment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221280%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Two%20MTA%20buses%20pass%20through%20Herald%20Square%20on%2034th%20Street%20in%20New%20York%20City.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F686592463d5881a51c1c95fb%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22853%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EWhen%20New%20York%20City%20experimented%20with%20five%20fare-free%20bus%20routes%2C%20assaults%20on%20bus%20drivers%20plummeted.%3Cp%3EGary%20Hershorn%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20MTA%20is%20already%20juggling%20a%20slew%20of%20urgent%20priorities%2C%20including%20desperately%20needed%20large-scale%20infrastructure%20improvement%20projects.%20Without%20a%20sustainable%20funding%20source%2C%20the%20program%20won't%20deliver%20what%20it%20promises%2C%20Zhan%20Guo%2C%20a%20professor%20of%20urban%20planning%20and%20transportation%20policy%20at%20NYU%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider.%20But%20Guo%20also%20wants%20to%20see%20more%20evidence%20that%20free%20buses%20would%20be%20more%20reliable%20and%20efficient%20than%20the%20current%20system.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20idea%20is%20very%20appealing%20to%20the%20general%20public%2C%20but%20I%20also%20feel%20there%20are%20actually%20many%20other%20options%20we%20haven't%20fully%20explored%20or%20utilized%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGuo%20thinks%20a%20Mamdani%20administration%20would%20be%20wise%20to%20start%20by%20expanding%20on%20the%20pilot%20program%20to%20test%20the%20waters.%20Regardless%20of%20whether%20Mamdani%20fulfills%20his%20key%20campaign%20promise%2C%20Guo%20said%2C%20it's%20a%20%26quot%3Bvery%20good%20time%20to%20talk%20about%20fare%20policy.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20like%20the%20fact%20that%20public%20transit%2C%20bus%20fares%2C%20such%20a%20very%20technical%20topic%2C%20became%20so%20visible%20in%20the%20mayor's%20campaign%2C%26quot%3B%20Guo%20said.%20%26quot%3BThis%20is%20actually%20a%20wonderful%20opportunity%20to%20engage%20the%20public.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%228dd277f1-2c7e-498f-a645-eb74c293f4bc%5C%22%3EHelping%20low-income%20New%20Yorkers%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EProponents%20of%20free%20buses%20point%20to%20a%20slew%20of%20potential%20upsides%20to%20the%20policy.%20For%20one%2C%20buses%20tend%20to%20serve%20neighborhoods%20with%20poor%20access%20to%20trains%20and%20low-income%20populations%20who%20could%20spend%20their%20savings%20from%20bus%20fares%20on%20other%20essentials.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELow-income%20New%20Yorkers%20are%20already%20eligible%20for%20half-price%20bus%20and%20subway%20fares%20through%20the%20MTA's%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nyc.gov%2Fsite%2Ffairfares%2Findex.page%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EFair%20Fares%20program%3C%2Fa%3E.%20But%20only%20about%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fsmhttp-ssl-58547.nexcesscdn.net%2Fnycss%2Fimages%2Fuploads%2Fpubs%2F031324_UHT2023_Transit_Brief_V6.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E38%25%20of%20eligible%20people%20use%20the%20program.%3C%2Fa%3E%20At%20the%20same%20time%2C%20nearly%20half%20of%20riders%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmetrics.mta.info%2F%3Fbus%2Ffareevasion%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eevade%20bus%20fares%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20costing%20the%20Metropolitan%20Transportation%20Authority%20%E2%80%94%20the%20state%20agency%20that%20runs%20the%20city's%20subways%20and%20buses%20%E2%80%94%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.mta.info%2Fdocument%2F111531%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehundreds%20of%20millions%20of%20dollars%20a%20year%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20equipment%20and%20personnel%20needed%20to%20collect%20fares%20are%20costly%2C%20too.%20Mamdani%20has%20pointed%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fwatch%3Fv%3DRScORcC0ssQ%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eto%20the%20Staten%20Island%20Ferry%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20has%20been%20free%20to%20ride%20for%20the%20last%20nearly%2020%20years%2C%20as%20an%20example%20of%20fare-free%20transit%2C%20which%20was%20made%20that%20way%20in%20part%20because%20collecting%20fares%20was%20too%20expensive.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMamdani%20and%20other%20supporters%20of%20the%20policy%20argue%20that%20buses%20can%20board%20passengers%20more%20efficiently%20without%20fares%2C%20keeping%20them%20on%20time%20and%20moving%20quickly%20while%20reducing%20conflict%20between%20bus%20drivers%20and%20riders%20evading%20the%20fare.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSome%20people%20see%20a%20tension%20between%20fast%20and%20free%20buses%2C%20but%20we%20shouldn't%20have%20to%20choose%2C%26quot%3B%20Danny%20Pearlstein%2C%20a%20spokesman%20for%20the%20grassroots%20transit%20group%20Riders%20Alliance%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider.%20%26quot%3BWe%20should%20be%20able%20to%20have%20both%20buses%20that%20move%20and%20buses%20that%20people%20can%20afford%20and%20that%20are%20worth%20paying%20for%2C%20even%20if%20not%20everyone%20or%20no%20one%20has%20to%20pay%20for%20them.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fzohran-mamdani-free-bus-kansas-city-new-york-city-2025-7%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1751530081000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F68658234f748d8c055f4da58%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22htt